I now have enough context. I can see the feedback log is very long (FB-224 is the newest). Let me now execute all three file changes:

---

## Diagnosis

The "Yilan Gao" logo text is wrapping to two lines under flex squeeze. The SCSS already has `flex-shrink: 0` on `.logo` and `white-space: nowrap` on the child `.logoText` span — but these two properties alone are insufficient. **The bug is that `white-space: nowrap` is on the child `<span>`, not on the `.logo` container itself.** The `.logo` element is `display: inline-flex`, and the flex algorithm can still compress an `inline-flex` container below its text content's natural width when only the *child* has `white-space: nowrap` — because the parent flex container's own intrinsic minimum size calculation doesn't propagate `white-space: nowrap` upward through the flex sizing algorithm. The container needs `white-space: nowrap` and `min-width: max-content` on itself to be iron-clad. The second deficiency: the right-side `.links` container has `min-width: 0` but not `overflow: hidden`, so browsers may still refuse to compress it past content minimum. The tagline `<span>` inside `.links` has `-webkit-line-clamp: 2` and `overflow: hidden` — which is correct — but if the tagline's own `min-width` resolves to a wide value before clamp kicks in, it pushes the logo.

## Root Cause

**AP-066: Unconstrained Flex Compression Breaking Identity Text.** The three-property shield (`white-space: nowrap` + `flex-shrink: 0` + `min-width: max-content`) must be applied to the **container element itself**, not only to a child `<span>`. Placing `white-space: nowrap` only on `.logoText` leaves the `.logo` flex container subject to the flex algorithm's intrinsic size negotiation, which can still collapse the container. AP-066 also lacks the explicit **identity-chrome priority rule** you're codifying: any element that is site identity (logo, wordmark, site name) must never yield to viewport pressure — the *surrounding chrome must absorb all compression*.

---

## Fix

### 1. `src/components/ui/Navigation/Navigation.module.scss`

```scss
@use '../../../styles' as *;

.nav {
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
  z-index: var(--portfolio-z-sticky);
  background-color: var(--portfolio-surface-terra-subtle);
  box-shadow: 0 4px 12px -4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);

  &::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 10px;
    transform: translateY(100%);
    backdrop-filter: blur(3px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(3px);
    mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2), transparent);
    -webkit-mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2), transparent);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
}

.navInner {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  max-width: $elan-container-wide;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: var(--portfolio-spacer-1-5x) var(--portfolio-spacer-2x);

  @media #{$elan-mq-sm} {
    padding: var(--portfolio-spacer-1-5x) var(--portfolio-spacer-4x);
  }
}

// ─── Identity-Chrome Priority Rule (AP-066) ───────────────────────────────────
// The logo is the site's core identity line. It must NEVER wrap or shrink under
// flex pressure at any viewport width.
//
// Three-property shield — ALL THREE must be on the container element itself,
// not on a child span:
//   1. flex-shrink: 0     — tells the flex algorithm this item does not give up space
//   2. white-space: nowrap — tells the container it must not wrap its own inline content
//   3. min-width: max-content — forces the flex base size to the logo's natural width,
//                              making flex-shrink: 0 meaningful even when flex-basis
//                              auto resolves narrow
//
// The tagline / links side MUST declare min-width: 0 + overflow: hidden so it
// absorbs ALL pressure that the logo refuses.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

.logo {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: $portfolio-spacer-0-5x;
  text-decoration: none;
  // Identity-chrome shield: all three properties on the container itself.
  flex-shrink: 0;
  white-space: nowrap;
  min-width: max-content;
  @include transition-fast;

  &:hover {
    .logoMark {
      background-color: var(--portfolio-text-neutral-max);
    }

    .logoText {
      color: var(--portfolio-text-neutral-max);
    }
  }
}

.logoMark {
  display: inline-block;
  height: calc($portfolio-type-2xl * 1.2);
  aspect-ratio: 1;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  background-color: $portfolio-accent-60;
  mask-image: url('/images/yg-logo.svg');
  mask-size: contain;
  mask-repeat: no-repeat;
  @include transition-fast;
}

.logoText {
  font-family: $portfolio-font-serif;
  font-size: $portfolio-type-2xl;
  font-weight: $portfolio-weight-regular;
  line-height: $portfolio-leading-snug;
  color: $portfolio-accent-60;
  letter-spacing: $portfolio-tracking-tight;
  white-space: nowrap; // belt-and-suspenders: also on the span
  @include transition-fast;
}

.links {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--portfolio-spacer-3x);
  // Soft edge of the nav: absorbs ALL compression that the logo refuses.
  // min-width: 0 allows flex children to shrink below their intrinsic width.
  // overflow: hidden prevents this container from ever expanding the nav row
  // beyond the viewport, which would push the logo off-screen instead.
  min-width: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.link {
  font-family: var(--portfolio-font-sans);
  font-size: var(--portfolio-type-sm);
  font-weight: var(--portfolio-weight-regular);
  color: var(--portfolio-text-secondary);
  text-decoration: none;
  @include transition-fast;

  &:hover {
    color: var(--portfolio-text-primary);
  }
}

.linkActive {
  color: var(--portfolio-text-primary);
  font-weight: var(--portfolio-weight-medium);
}

.tagline {
  @include body-sm;
  color: var(--portfolio-text-secondary);
  // Soft edge: yields to narrow viewports by wrapping onto a second line,
  // capped at two lines so it never invades the site content below.
  min-width: 0;
  text-align: right;
  display: -webkit-box;
  -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
  -webkit-line-clamp: 2;
  line-clamp: 2;
  overflow: hidden;
}
```

**The three changes in this file:**
1. `white-space: nowrap` moved to `.logo` container (in addition to `.logoText`)
2. `min-width: max-content` added to `.logo` container
3. `overflow: hidden` added to `.links` — seals off the soft side so no child inside `.links` can ever force the row wider and thereby displace the logo

