```markdown
<a id="fb-146"></a>
### FB-146: Nav logo "Yilan Gao" wrapping to two lines under squeeze

**Status: RESOLVED**
**Date:** [original date]
**Component:** `src/components/ui/Navigation/Navigation.module.scss`

**Feedback:** At viewports narrower than ~520px (or any time the browser window is squeezed), the "Yilan Gao" wordmark wraps to two lines. This must never happen — the logo is the core identity line and is not a soft element.

**Root cause:** AP-066. `white-space: nowrap` was on `.logoText` (child `<span>`) but not on the `.logo` container element (`<a>`). The flex algorithm can still compress an `inline-flex` container even when its child has `white-space: nowrap`, because the container's own intrinsic minimum size is still negotiable. `flex-shrink: 0` without `min-width: max-content` also fails when `flex-basis: auto` resolves to a narrow value.

**Fix applied:**
```scss
// On .logo container:
flex-shrink: 0;
white-space: nowrap;      // moved to container, not just child span
min-width: max-content;   // new — locks flex base to natural rendered width

// On .links (soft side):
overflow: hidden;          // new — seals compression into the soft side
```

**Identity-Chrome Priority Rule extracted:** Logo, wordmark, and site name MUST NEVER yield to viewport pressure at any width. The tagline and personal blurb CAN wrap to two lines — they are the soft edge. This rule is now the primary principle in AP-066.

**See:** AP-066
```

---

## Principle

**AP-066 — Identity-Chrome Priority Rule.** The three-property shield (`flex-shrink: 0` + `white-space: nowrap` + `min-width: max-content`) must be applied to the **container element itself**, not to child spans. The soft side must declare both `min-width: 0` AND `overflow: hidden` to fully absorb pressure. This is not a preference — it is a hard invariant: identity chrome never yields; surrounding chrome always absorbs.

